# Folder and feature layout

## Feature-first structure

- Organize product code by feature under `src/features/{FeatureName}` (and route-owned code under `src/app/`) instead of grouping unrelated UI by technical layer only.
- Prefer PascalCase directories and files for components; camelCase for utilities; kebab-case for configuration files.

## Components and subcomponents

- Place each component with stories, tests, or multiple files in its own folder. Keep tightly coupled, tiny helpers in the same folder when splitting would only add navigation cost (YAGNI).
- Name subcomponent directories `components/`. Avoid `views`, `containers`, `presenters`, or other alternate folder names.
- For complex trees, use a predictable layout:
  - `ComponentName/ComponentName.tsx`
  - Co-located `ComponentName.test.tsx`, `ComponentName.stories.tsx`, optional `ComponentName.mdx`
  - Nested `components/` for real subcomponents with the same pattern

## Hooks and utilities

- When a hook grows multiple helpers, move helpers under `HookName/utils/` with one focused module per file and keep `HookName.ts` as the orchestrating hook.
- Prefer verb–noun utility names (`buildLogoutLink`, `normalizeTariffDTO`). Avoid vague names like `process` or `handleData`.

## Types and constants

- Store reusable types as `*.type.ts` in `types/` folders next to their feature.
- Put static maps (`Record<Enum, …>`), registries, and feature constants in `*.constant.ts` or similarly named map modules—not buried inside unrelated components.

## Tests and fixtures

- Co-locate tests with the code under test.
- Store snapshots in `__snapshots__/`.
- Keep shared fixtures near the feature that owns them.

## Imports

- Prefer path aliases (`@/…`) for shared modules; use relative imports inside a feature’s boundary.
- Create barrels or lazy indexes only for documented reasons (multi-export surface, lazy loading boundaries). Do not add index files that only obscure one component.

## Documentation per feature

- Add `development.mdx` for complex features to explain architecture, data flow, and extension points.

## MDX documentation shape

- Use the section headings **Description**, **Usage**, and **Preview** only.
- Do not paste full `import` statements inside TypeScript snippets; show usage readers can paste without redundant import noise.
- Mirror the structural example in `app/components/ActiveIndicator/ActiveIndicator.mdx` when authoring new MDX docs.
